  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Overcoming Stigma of Disabilities in South Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children with disabilities, their parents and caregivers in rural areas of South Africa have limited access to the medical care they need. Well-designed wheelchairs are key to achieving independence and social inclusion. A shortage of trained caregivers, lack of funding by the government, and lack of understanding about disabilities also create challenges. Through Uhambo&apos;s grassroots and holistic programs, some of the most vulnerable people in the world, children with disabilities, are served.</narrative>
  </description>
